# ===========================================================================
%NAME Samples2, Suite 1: addresses acme subset
# ===========================================================================
%DESCRIPTION
# ??????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????
Execute a query on the "all_addresses" view in VDP. This view is a union of
the "address" table in the "acme" datasource and also the "address" table
in the "sakila" datasource, which had to be previously joined with other
two tables in sakila containing info for cities and countries.

In this case, the idea is to test that all the addresses in "acme" are
actually a subset of the addresses we can access from the union view in VDP.
Note the "type:subset" context property at the %RESULTS directive.
# ===========================================================================
%EXECUTION[query]
{ ds:vdp }
SELECT DISTINCT street, city, zip, country
FROM all_addresses
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
%RESULTS[query]
{
  ds:acme,
  ordered:no,
  type:subset
}
SELECT DISTINCT street, city, zip, country
FROM address
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
